Fubu
[[Image:Fubu.gif|thumb|right|A young nigra wearing the badge of his entitlement proudly.]]
;F.U.B.U. :A popular black person apparel line. The letters stand for "Farmers Used to Beat Us", a mantra chanted by members of the black subculture and, in particular, [[NAACP|certain organizations]] within it with the implication that they are entitled to benefits or "reparations" for the misdeeds of earlier generations of [[The Man]].
{{stub}}